Sentencas: The electrochemical performance of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) is highly reliant upon the properties of cathodes, including crystal structure, electrical conductivity, electrode thickness, and so on.
Titulo: Thickness-dependent high-performance solid oxide fuel cells with Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode

Sentencas: Here, Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta (BSCF) is synthesized and served as the electrode for enabling high-performance SOFCs.
Titulo: Thickness-dependent high-performance solid oxide fuel cells with Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode

Sentencas: The effect of electrode thickness on the electrocatalytic activity is systematically investigated.
Titulo: Thickness-dependent high-performance solid oxide fuel cells with Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode

Sentencas: The electrode thickness is adjusted in two ways.
Titulo: Thickness-dependent high-performance solid oxide fuel cells with Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode

Sentencas: One is spray-coating and then calcining once, and the other is performing the above process twice.
Titulo: Thickness-dependent high-performance solid oxide fuel cells with Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode

Sentencas: On the basis of symmetrical cells configuration, the oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) activity of BSCF electrode with different thickness is evaluated and analyzed by the electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) technique and distribution of relaxation time (DRT).
Titulo: Thickness-dependent high-performance solid oxide fuel cells with Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode

Sentencas: The obtained area-specific resistances (ASRs) of electrodes on the oxygen ion conducting electrolyte Sm0.2Ce0.9O1.90 (SDC) demonstrate the thickness-dependent electrochemical activity in ORR of BSCF electrode.
Titulo: Thickness-dependent high-performance solid oxide fuel cells with Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode

Sentencas: With an electrode thickness of 24 mu m that controlled by conducting spray-coating and calcining twice, the BSCF electrode displays the optimal electrochemical performance with an ASR of 0.072 Omega cm(2) in ambient air at 600 degrees C.
Titulo: Thickness-dependent high-performance solid oxide fuel cells with Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode

Sentencas: This strategy has allowed us to produce an electrode layer with optimal thickness, paving a new path for the design of high-performance SOFCs.
Titulo: Thickness-dependent high-performance solid oxide fuel cells with Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode
